# Busani, Republic of Buryatia

}}
Busani () is a rural locality (a settlement) in Bauntovsky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. The population was 35 as of 2010. There is 1 street.
Geography
Busani is located by lake Busani and to the south of Uakit village, 97&nbsp;km north of Bagdarin (the district's administrative centre) by road.
